Package com.mvp4g.client.annotation.module

Annotation Types Summary
AfterLoadChildModule This annotation can be used to annotate the method of an event in your EventBus interface.
BeforeLoadChildModule This annotation can be used to annotate the method of an event in your EventBus interface.
ChildModule This annotation can be used as an attribute of the ChildModules annotation to add a child module to the parent module.

The following attributes can be defined:
moduleClass: class of the child module async: if true, GWT2 code splitting feature will be used to load the code of the child module.
ChildModules This annotation can be used to add child modules to a parent module.
DisplayChildModuleView This annotation can be used to annotate the method of an event in your EventBus interface.
HistoryName This annotation should be used when a child module wants to store events in the history browser.
LoadChildModuleError This annotation can be used to annotate the method of an event in your EventBus interface.
